Content:
[telegram] <Regnar> 1.Agama lite mode uses SPV single address, you use your seed (or pin if you set it up) to access your address, one KMD address per seed. Agama Native can have multiple addresses as well as Z addresses. 
2. Komodo has two types of addresses, transparent addresses are most common, they are the ones you claim rewards in, and can see balances etc they begin with R, and are often referred to as R addresses. There are also 'Zs' addresses or Z addresses, these are private addresses where balances do not show up on chains. They also make Z transactions where the amount and addresses aren't visible either. These Z addresses however, are being moved to a parallel chain soon, so I wouldn't  mess with them right now. What I mean by this is Komodo uses multi-chain infrastructure, it's how they scale, so Z transactions are going onto a new parallel chain along with new Crypto Conditions smart contracts. This swapping between parallel chains will be seamless and using Komodos MoMoM tech to ensure fungible coins and keep supply consistent. (re @TonyStarkBR: Being new to KMD, I have some doubts:
1) Agama wallet (SPV mode) uses a single, fixed address? It seems to me so...
2) what kind of addresses do we have and how to recognize them?)
